-- New South Wales Says Due Diligence Started Today on Energy Businesses
-- Victoria Batchelor
-- 2010-07-01T06:02:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/new-south-wales-says-due-diligence-started-today-on-energy-businesses.html

          
          
             The New South Wales state government
said due diligence started today on the government’s retail
electricity businesses and Gentrader contracts.  
 “The government will require binding bids from potential
acquirers by Nov. 1 with the transactions to be executed by the
end of the year,” state Treasurer Eric Roozendaal said in a
statement e-mailed to Bloomberg News.  
          
          


  


        